  "pr_number": 10130,
  "issue_number": 6540,
  "issue_title": "Database Backend Should Support the retry config parameters",
  "issue_body": "# Checklist\n<!--\nTo check an item on the list replace [ ] with [x].\n-->\n\n* [x] I have checked the [issues list](https://github.com/celery/celery/issues?q=is%3Aissue+label%3A%22Issue+Type%3A+Enhancement%22+-label%3A%22Category%3A+Documentation%22)\n  for similar or identical enhancement to an existing feature.\n* [x] I have checked the [pull requests list](https://github.com/celery/celery/pulls?q=is%3Apr+label%3A%22Issue+Type%3A+Enhancement%22+-label%3A%22Category%3A+Documentation%22)\n  for existing proposed enhancements.\n* [x] I have checked the [commit log](https://github.com/celery/celery/commits/master)\n  to find out if the if the same enhancement was already implemented in the\n  master branch.\n* [x] I have included all related issues and possible duplicate issues in this issue\n      (If there are none, check this box anyway).\n\n## Related Issues and Possible Duplicates\n#### Related Issues\n* None\n\n#### Possible Duplicates\n* None\n\n# Brief Summary\nThe `DatabaseBackend` should use the `BasedBackend` retry logic and remove the existing retry behavior. The PR https://github.com/celery/celery/pull/6122 introduced the following params:\n\n\n* `result_backend_always_retry` \n* `result_backend_max_sleep_between_retries_ms`\n* `result_backend_base_sleep_between_retries_ms` \n* `result_backend_max_retries` \n\nThis is a lot more control that currently exists with the current database backend:\nhttps://github.com/celery/celery/blob/8bceb446e6a07682d4b8dd6199cdac450bd63578/celery/backends/database/**init**.py#L39-L60\n\nThere is currently some discrepancies between the `BaseBackend` retries and the `DatabaseBackend` retries. Specifically the methods for `save_group`, `restore_group`, `delete_group`, and forget have retries in the `DatabaseBackend` while the `BaseBackend` does not. This needs to be resolved before the `DatabaseBackend` retries can be removed.\n\n# Design\nThe design work has already been done in PR https://github.com/celery/celery/pull/6122. \n\n## Architectural Considerations\nDo any other backends need to be touched up to fully support the config?\n\n## Proposed Behavior\nUsed the configuration for the how the backend should retry in the database backend. This will require implementing the method `exception_safe_to_retry`.\n\n## Proposed UI/UX\nN/A \n\n## Diagrams\nN/A\n\n\n## Alternatives\nNone\n\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-03-01T09:45:29Z",
